========================================
gstack — Garry Tan
========================================

Loom's judgment layer, ship-engineer cluster, retrospective ceremony,
browser daemon foundation, and direct-symlink distribution path were
adapted from Garry Tan's gstack (https://github.com/garrytan/gstack)
under the terms of gstack's published license. Per the M-13 gstack-
adoption locked decision, every idea was re-authored as a Loom-native
resource (agent / prompt / protocol / skill / infrastructure); no gstack
code was copied verbatim.

The following thirteen milestones and thirty-six features are attributed
to gstack as the source of the underlying idea (see
planning/ROADMAP-gstack-adoption.md for the one-to-one mapping):

  M-01 Learnings + regressions registry     (.loom/learnings.toon,
                                             .loom/regressions.toon,
                                             /loom-learn)
  M-02 Retrospective ceremony               (/loom-retro)
  M-03 Pre-plan think + spec                (/loom-think, /loom-spec)
  M-04 Planning reviewers                   (plan-ceo-review-agent,
                                             plan-eng-review-agent,
                                             plan-design-review-agent,
                                             plan-devex-review-agent)
  M-05 Code review lenses                   (code-design-review-agent
                                             with AI-slop detection,
                                             code-llm-trust-review-agent,
                                             code-codex-review-agent)
  M-06 Design build                         (/loom-design:consultation,
                                             /loom-design:html,
                                             /loom-design:shotgun)
  M-07 Doc lifecycle                        (/loom-docs:generate,
                                             /loom-docs:release)
  M-08 Codebase-design vocabulary adoption  (composes with the Matt
                                             Pocock attribution above)
  M-09 Cross-worktree fan-in coordination   (/loom-worktree,
                                             worktree-lease schema)
  M-10 Ship engineer                        (/loom-ship, /loom-canary,
                                             /loom-landing-report,
                                             /loom-setup:deploy,
                                             VERSION-slot registry)
  M-11 Browser infrastructure               (/loom-browser daemon,
                                             /loom-qa, cookie import)
  M-12 Benchmarking                         (/loom-benchmark:models,
                                             /loom-benchmark:perf)
  M-13 Distribution overhaul + capstone     (/loom-install direct-
                                             symlink path, capstone
                                             feature F-37)

Also attributed to gstack, adopted as cross-cutting principles rather
than as milestone features:

  - Confidence-calibrated finding scoring (confidence:1-10) applied
    across all reviewer AgentResult envelopes.
  - Decision Principles + Mechanical / Taste / User-Challenge
    classifier consumed by every auto-flow agent
    (protocols/loom-decision-principles.md).
  - The 0-10 rate + prescribe-to-10 rubric shape used in
    protocols/roadmap-rubrics/*.md.
  - The plan-completion audit classifier
    (DIFF-VERIFIABLE / CROSS-REPO / EXTERNAL-STATE / CONTENT-SHAPE)
    inlined into /loom-ship PR bodies.
  - The security-review two-tier model (daily 8/10 gate + monthly
    2/10 deep-scan) used by /loom-cso.

gstack itself is an opinionated, rigorously documented methodology worth
reading directly; we recommend it as a companion reference to anyone
building agentic tooling on Claude Code.
